defaultGovernment needs to outline its funding plans for industrial CCS.
default1.2.default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
default The lack of CCS transport and storage infrastructure is a significant barrier to UK CCS development.
default1.3.default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
default Government needs to retain manufacturing industry in the UK so that when CCS hubs are developed their benefit is maximized.
default1.4.default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
default The UK cement industry GHG 2
default050 Roadmap outlines the importance of CCS to the cement industry. There will be a shortfall in decarbonisation without CCS.
default1.5.default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
default The financial barriers are significant. A CCS cement plant will be double the costs of a non-CCS equivalent. Government funding is
default needed to navigate the CCS financial barriers. 
default1.6.default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
default For industries with high process emissions that are not related to combustion, CCS may be the only option for significant decarbonisation.
default1.7.default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
default The UK is lagging behind other countries in developing industrial 
defaultCCS in the cement industry.
