default&#xa0; 
defaultCould the successful development of CCS impdefaultrove international efforts to mitigate climate change? What role could UK CCS play in this?default10.1.default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe UK must play its part in addressing climate change 
defaultbut should not place costs on energy consumers that are not faced by competing nations. The power generation sector will pass on the costs of CCS to consumers, including its industrial consumers that are most vulnerable (in terms of carbon leakage) to the 
defaultprice increases. 
default&#xa0;default 
default10.2.default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe UK CCS programme has to ensure that industrial consumers are shielded from the costs of CCS in power generation in the transition to a low carbon economy.
